<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,757,258,955]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
Tympanal organs (
<figureCitation box="[355,474,386,409]" captionStart="Figs 21 - 25" captionStartId="6.[151,192,1998,2019]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,257,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[166,1422,257,1950]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 21 - 25. Aurotalis spp., female genitalia and tympanal organs. (21) A. delicatalis (Hampson), female, RSA. (22) A. dionisa Błeszyński, female, Namibia. (23) A. dionisa Błeszyński, male, Namibia. (24) A. cristata sp. n., female paratype, RSA. (25) A. dicksoni sp. n., male paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/306816/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Fig. 23-25</figureCitation>
). Transverse ridge round- ed. Tympanic bridge well developed, lightly sclerotized. Tympanic drum ovoid. Venulae secundae well developed, concave. The well developed and lightly sclerotized tympanic bridge seems to be the more constant feature through the genus, other characteristics being rather variable.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,757,258,955]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[324,395,610,635]" captionStart="Figs 7 - 9" captionStartId="3.[153,194,2018,2039]" captionTargetBox="[197,1396,1037,1952]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1399,1030,1952]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 7 - 9. Crambinae spp., male genitalia, differences among close genera. (7) Ancylolomia planicosta Martin, RSA. (8) Prionotalis balia (Tams), Tanzania. (9) Aurotalis cristata sp. n., Zimbabwe. Arrow = valva; flash arrow = vinculum; thick bar = tegumen" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/306806/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Figs 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[409,473,611,635]" captionStart="Figs 13 - 20" captionStartId="5.[151,192,1940,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1427,947,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[148,1439,933,1898]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13 - 20. Aurotalis spp., genitalia and male abdominal segment VIII. (13) A. dionisa Błeszyński, male genitalia, Namibia. (14) The same, phallus. (15) A. delicatalis (Hampson), RSA, phallus extracted on the right. (16) A. delicatalis, sclerotizations of abdominal segment VIII. (17) A. cristata sp. n., Zimbabwe, sclerotizations of abdominal segment VIII. (18) A. dionisa Błeszyński, Namibia, sclerotizations of abdominal segment VIII. (19) A. nigrisquamalis (Hampson), Swaziland, sclerotizations of abdominal segment VIII. (20) The same, female genitalia, RSA." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/306812/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">13-15</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[487,602,610,635]" captionStart="Figs 26 - 30" captionStartId="7.[151,192,1996,2017]" captionTargetBox="[191,1408,1019,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,1007,1963]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 26 - 30. Aurotalis spp., genitalia and abdominal segment VIII. (26) A. cristata sp. n., holotype, on the right juxta and phallus. (27) A. cristata sp. n., female paratype, Zimbabwe. (28) A. argyrastis (Hampson), holotype. (29) A. dicksoni sp. n., male paratype, on the right juxta and phallus. (30) A. dicksoni sp. n., sclerotizations of abdominal segment VIII. Scale: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/306820/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">26, 29, 30</figureCitation>
): Uncus more or less apically downcurved. Gnathos strongly upcurved while being straight, simple or bifid. Tegumen and valva stout being tapering. Vinculum without or with small dorsal projection. Pseudosaccus small. Phallus stout to elongate, with maximum two cornuti.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,757,258,955]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[341,423,802,827]" captionStart="Figs 10 - 12" captionStartId="4.[151,192,1996,2017]" captionTargetBox="[226,1376,1023,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1000,1950]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 10 - 12. Crambinae spp., female genitalia, differences among close genera. (10) Ancylolomia planicosta Martin, Tanzania. (11) Prionotalis balia (Tams), Tanzania. (12) Aurotalis cristata sp. n., paratype, Zimbabwe. Arrow = papillae anales; thick bar = ostium bursae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/306809/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Figs 12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[434,498,803,827]" captionStart-0="Figs 13 - 20" captionStart-1="Figs 21 - 25" captionStartId-0="5.[151,192,1940,1961]" captionStartId-1="6.[151,192,1998,2019]" captionTargetBox-0="[172,1427,947,1884]" captionTargetBox-1="[166,1421,257,1946]" captionTargetId-0="figure@5.[148,1439,933,1898]" captionTargetId-1="figure@6.[166,1422,257,1950]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="6" captionText-0="Figs 13 - 20. Aurotalis spp., genitalia and male abdominal segment VIII. (13) A. dionisa Błeszyński, male genitalia, Namibia. (14) The same, phallus. (15) A. delicatalis (Hampson), RSA, phallus extracted on the right. (16) A. delicatalis, sclerotizations of abdominal segment VIII. (17) A. cristata sp. n., Zimbabwe, sclerotizations of abdominal segment VIII. (18) A. dionisa Błeszyński, Namibia, sclerotizations of abdominal segment VIII. (19) A. nigrisquamalis (Hampson), Swaziland, sclerotizations of abdominal segment VIII. (20) The same, female genitalia, RSA." captionText-1="Figs 21 - 25. Aurotalis spp., female genitalia and tympanal organs. (21) A. delicatalis (Hampson), female, RSA. (22) A. dionisa Błeszyński, female, Namibia. (23) A. dionisa Błeszyński, male, Namibia. (24) A. cristata sp. n., female paratype, RSA. (25) A. dicksoni sp. n., male paratype." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/306812/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/306816/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">20-22</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[509,578,802,827]" captionStart="Figs 26 - 30" captionStartId="7.[151,192,1996,2017]" captionTargetBox="[191,1408,1019,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,1007,1963]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 26 - 30. Aurotalis spp., genitalia and abdominal segment VIII. (26) A. cristata sp. n., holotype, on the right juxta and phallus. (27) A. cristata sp. n., female paratype, Zimbabwe. (28) A. argyrastis (Hampson), holotype. (29) A. dicksoni sp. n., male paratype, on the right juxta and phallus. (30) A. dicksoni sp. n., sclerotizations of abdominal segment VIII. Scale: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/306820/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">27, 28</figureCitation>
): Papillae anales with strong setae on upper surface, originating from tips of short projection of highly corrugated membrane. Both apophyses strongly developed. Ostium bursae and sterigma membranous. Corpus bursae suboval, without signa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
